This paper deals with maximum likelihood learning in graphical models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) inference, which is a popular method in data science (cs.DS). The concept of fast-mixing parameter sets is related to information theory (cs.IT) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
